name: RuPaul's Drag Race Down Under
overview: Drag queen contestants compete in an elimination-style contest and strut their stuff in a variety of challenges - all to prove that they’ve got what it takes to be Down Under's next Drag Queen Superstar!

production_companies.name: Warner Bros. International Television Production New Zealand

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: RuPaul is seeking out the very best in Australasian drag as the brightest in Aussie and Kiwi talent compete for the title of the Down Under’s Next Drag Superstar. Each week the queens are given outrageous challenges that test their fashion, acting, dancing, singing, and comedy skills.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Mama Ru returns for more shenanigans as ten new queens from all across Australia & New Zealand compete for the title of Down Under’s Next Drag Superstar, and this time there’s a $50k cash prize at stake!

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: This electrifying competition series brings together the most dazzling drag queens from Australia and New Zealand for a no-holds-barred battle to be crowned the next drag superstar. This season promises to be an absolute riot of outrageous fashion, jaw-dropping performances, and plenty of drama and laughs along the way. From the wild and wonderful challenges to the larger-than-life personalities of the contestants, you won't be able to tear your eyes away from the screen.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: Drag Race returns with new host Michelle Visage, as ten new queens from all across Australia & New Zealand compete for the title of Down Under’s Next Drag Superstar.

episodes.name: G'day G'day G'day
episodes.overview: We meet the Australian and New Zealand Drag Queens who will be competing to become Down Under’s first Drag Race Superstar. It’s a hometown homage this week, as the Queens showcase their personalities in the ‘get to know you’ Ball.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The queens don their best celebrity get-up to compete in the infamous celebrity impression Olympics. It’s Snatch Game, baby!

episodes.name: Queens Down Under
episodes.overview: RuPaul announced the queens will be working together to debut a brand new drag anthem, "Queens Down Under". Drama flared up between Elektra and her teammates, Karen, Kita and Maxi, just to psyche the others. The queens received a video message from Troye Sivan and Leland for songwriting tips.

episodes.name: Rucycled
episodes.overview: The queens are put through their paces with a sewing challenge that has them showcasing their best thrift flip.

episodes.name: Yeast Spread
episodes.overview: The queens put their marketing hats on, as they are challenged to create and market a product, green screen infomercial and all.

episodes.name: Family Resemblance
episodes.overview: Can you see the family resemblance? The queens are challenged to makeover and raise their very own Drag family members, out of drag first timers.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: The grand finale crowns the first ever winner of RuPaul’s Drag Race Down Under. The remaining queens must write their own verses to RuPaul’s I'm a Winner, Baby.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: RuPaul is seeking out the very best in Australasian drag as the brightest in Aussie and Kiwi talent compete for the title of the Down Under’s Next Drag Superstar. Each week the queens are given outrageous challenges that test their fashion, acting, dancing, singing, and comedy skills.

episodes.name: Grand Opening
episodes.overview: The queens are thrown in at the deep end as they’re tasked with creating fashion forward garments out of recyclable and natural materials.

episodes.name: Cagey Queens
episodes.overview: The queens are split into two groups before their acting chops are put to the test in original screenplay ‘Caged Queens’, a prison-based dramedy.

episodes.name: A Bottomless Brunch
episodes.overview: The queens pair up as they harness their hosting skills in a Drag Brunch style challenge.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The queens have to impersonate celebrities in the legendary Snatch Game.

episodes.name: Bosom Buddies
episodes.overview: The queens have to choose their own teams as they write and record verses that throw shade to their own band members in this week’s girl group challenge.

episodes.name: Hometown Hunnies
episodes.overview: The queens have to sell themselves while creating an advertisement that showcases the main tourist attractions of their hometowns.

episodes.name: Drag Family Makeover
episodes.overview: The queens are challenged to transform a family of men into gorgeous glamazons.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: The final three queens write and record their own verses to RuPaul’s “Who is She” as they prepare to perform on the mainstage for the last time, competing for the title of the Next Drag Superstar!

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: Mama Ru returns for more shenanigans as ten new queens from all across Australia & New Zealand compete for the title of Down Under’s Next Drag Superstar, and this time there’s a $50k cash prize at stake!

episodes.name: Mardi Gras Pride
episodes.overview: Mama Ru returns as ten new queens from all across Australia and New Zealand compete for the title of Down Under's Next Drag Superstar. For their first challenge, the queens throw a Mardi Gras Pride-themed celebration on the main stage.

episodes.name: Muriel's Bedding
episodes.overview: The queens are invited to Muriel’s Wedding – but without a thing to wear, they must design their wedding couture from leftover bedding materials.

episodes.name: Fake Housewives of Down Under
episodes.overview: The queens split into teams as they improv their way through a reunion special of The Fake Housewives of Down Under.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The queens have to impersonate celebrities in the legendary Snatch Game.

episodes.name: BMX Bitches
episodes.overview: Inspired by the campy ‘80s film “BMX Bandits” the queens write original lyrics, sing and dance as two rival girl groups.

episodes.name: Drag Brunch
episodes.overview: The queens are showcasing their charisma, uniqueness, nerve and talents at the annual Drag Brunch.

episodes.name: Terriers in Tiaras
episodes.overview: The queens makeover dog lovers and their fur babies into drag divas.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: As their final challenge, the top three queens collaborate on a new remix of RuPaul’s “Crying on the Dancefloor." And RuPaul crowns Down Under's Next Drag Superstar.
